We recommended that the Local Chief Executive and the MENRO:

a. secure the approved copy of the Ten-Year Solid Waste Management Plan; 

b. provide a specific budget for the Solid Waste Programs and Activities; 

c. avail of the fund set aside as Solid Waste Management Fund in the National Treasury pursuant to Section 46 of R.A. No. 9003, upon receipt of the approved copy of the plan; 

d. strictly enforce the use of Material Recovery Facility down to the barangay levels; 

e. make a clear proposal to the Sangguniang Bayan for the campaign on the “no segregation, no collection policy and the “no-littering policy” among the residents and tourists; 

f. effect immediate closure of the dumpsite operating at the Brgy. Niyugan; and 

g. finalize the contract with Metro Clark Waste Management Corporation for the hauling of the existing waste being kept at a temporary Residual Containment Area.
